verses.roman:
ei-mata mahāprabhu pāñā cetana
snāna kari' kaila jagannātha-daraśana

synonyms: ei-mata—in this way; mahāprabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; pāñā cetana—becoming conscious; snāna kari'-after bathing; kaila jagannātha-daraśana—saw Lord Jagannātha.
translation: Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu thus returned to consciousness. He then bathed and went to see Lord Jagannātha.
